1782 ✗ SUBROUTINE SPOLE(ix,im,RLAT,PHIR,utsec,SDA,PHIMR,ESSA,CMORG)
1783 implicit none
1784 real, PARAMETER ::PI=3.141592653,DTR=PI/180.
1785 integer,intent(in) :: ix ! longitude dimension
1786 integer,intent(in) :: im ! number of longitude
1787 real, intent(in) :: rlat(im) !geo latitude (rad)
1788 real, intent(in) :: phir(im) !geo longitude (rad)
1789 real, intent(in) :: utsec !UT second
1790 real, intent(in) :: sda !solar declination angle (rad)
1791 real, intent(out):: phimr(im) !maglongitude (rad)
1792 real, intent(out):: essa(im) !magnetic local time
1793 real, intent(out):: cmorg(im)
1794 ! local variables
1795 ✗ real th,th1,phi1,sinth,sinth1,costh1,sinph1,cosph1,ac1,bc1,cc1, &
1796 ✗ & ac2,bc2,cc2,phim,ssp,sspr,csda,as1,bs1,cs1,as2,bs2,cs2,gml, &
1797 & cmag
1798 ✗ integer i
1799 !
1800 ✗ do i=1,im
1801 ✗ th=pi/2.-rlat(i)
1802 !
1803 ! SET POLE COORD. FOR EACH HEMIS.
1804 !
1805 ✗ IF (RLAT(i).GE.0.0) THEN
1806 ✗ TH1=9.25*DTR
1807 ✗ PHI1=-78.0*DTR
1808 ELSE
1809 ✗ TH1=16.32*DTR
1810 ✗ PHI1=-54.0*DTR
1811 END IF
1812 !
1813 ✗ SINTH=SIN(TH)
1814 ✗ SINTH1=SIN(TH1)
1815 ✗ COSTH1=COS(TH1)
1816 ✗ SINPH1=SIN(PHI1)
1817 ✗ COSPH1=COS(PHI1)
1818 !
1819 ! do i=1,im
1820 ✗ AC1=SINTH*COS(PHIR(i))
1821 ✗ BC1=SINTH*SIN(PHIR(i))
1822 ✗ CC1=COS(TH)
